{
  "stem": "21786.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "B- O, there's two O, H-M-E-N.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And capital M-A, those two things on it, H-R-E-N with a special kind of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] ruler over the-- over this territory called the protectorate.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was the protector.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "His name was Heydrich, H-E-Y-D-R-I-C-H, who was known as 'the butcher.' He was, in the Nazi hierarchy, about number three after Hitler.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was considered to be become eventually the Hitler successor, for he was relatively young.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, the Department for the Solution of the Jewish Question moved to Prague with the army and with the SS.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the-- they simply were preparing to make the territory free of Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Judenrein, J-U-D-E-N-R-E-I-N.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was the goal of any part of Germany or the occupied territories.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They do it-- did it in a way that they themselves ordered the Jewish community or, as it was called at that point in time, the Council of the Elders to prepare for eventual transportation of the Jews out of Prague or out of the territory, out of the territory of the protectorate.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it started in 1940 when a few transports were sent to Upper Silezia, S-I-L-E-Z-I-A, which was part of Poland at that point.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then they sent a huge transport from Prague, 5,000 people, to Lodz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's in Poland.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It's this L-- cut through and pronounced in a soft way, 'lah--' O-D-Z.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Germans called it Litzmanstadt, L-I-T-Z-M-A-N-S-T-A-D-T.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And from then on, every week or every two weeks usually 1,000 or 2,000 people were sent to first to different places in Poland, in 1940, 1941, 1942.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In 1941, they started to send people to a-- a fortress, which was built under the reign of Empress Maria Theresa.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] You'll spell.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
